Task: Implement the "Switch" logic for the Environment sub-tabs and build out the specific technical content for each view.
​1. Functional Tab Switcher:
​In the Environments component, use a useState variable activeSubTab.
​Update the sub-nav buttons so clicking them sets the activeSubTab.
​Use a switch or mapping object to render the specific component for each tab (e.g., <PodsView />, <DeploymentsView />).
​2. The "Hirer's Choice" Requirements:
​Deployments Tab (Image 11): >     - Create a "Start New Deployment" card with 4 <select> elements.
​Sequential Logic: Provider is disabled until Pipeline is chosen. Repository is disabled until Provider is chosen.
​Alert: If "GitHub" is the provider, show a Red Banner: "⚠️ No account connected. [Link GitHub Account]".
​Pods & Nodes Tabs: >     - Display a table with columns: Name, Status, CPU, RAM.
​Use a useEffect with a setInterval to make the CPU numbers move (e.g., 42.1% -> 43.5%) so the page feels "Live."
​Use a pulsing green dot for the "Running" status.
​Firewall Tab (Image 13): >     - Show a table of whitelisted IPs.
​Add an input field with a button "Add My Current IP" that auto-fills a mock IP address.
​Diagnostics Tab: >     - Create a "Terminal" UI (black background, green/white text).
​Add a "Run Health Check" button that "streams" text lines: > Verifying SSL... OK, > Checking Database... OK.
​3. Brand Refinement:
​The Orange Link Rule: Ensure all technical IDs (e.g., env-3029) and Website names are rendered in Corefinity Orange and are clickable.
​Breadcrumbs: Make the top breadcrumb dynamic: All Clients > Example Company > [Active Sub-Tab].
